Nairobi will play host to the 5th annual China trade week from 5th to 12th June at the Kenyatta International Convention Center. Some 600 exhibitors are expected and at least 30,000 local and international visitors. The conference will cover imports, exports, and capital goods. According to the Kenya National Bureau of Statistics, the value of imports from China in 2018 reached 371 billion shillings compared to 11 billion shillings worth of exports to Beijing.